content_english:
@VietnamRoadTrip Actually, many people get excited about imports, but you also have to look at whether they're Japanese or Thai imports; Indonesian or Malay imports aren't any better than what we assemble in Vietnam... Vietnam's skill level in the region is often only behind Thailand's!
I remember I went out with two friends who have Japanese imports from 2016, and I have to say they've never broken down, but wear-and-tear items like tires, brake pads... you just have to replace them when needed!
So the other day when I heard the price of the Japanese-imported Subaru Crosstrek, I didn't think it was overpriced at all. Too bad it only seats 5!
